Sentencas: The superfine crystallites of Nd(1.8)Ce(0.2)CuO(4+delta)are obtained when prepared by mechanochemical reaction using different process control agents.
Titulo: Cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The crystallite size, C-s = 34 am is the smallest for Nd1.8Ce0.2CuO4+delta prepared using salicylic acid process control agent (NCCO(Sa)) as compared to others.
Titulo: Cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The dc conductivity (1.64 S cm(-1)) is the highest for NCCO(Sa) amongst all, which is attributed to the smallest crystallite size and high sintered density.
Titulo: Cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The agglomeration of superfine grains leads to optimal distribution of nano-pores results in low area specific resistance (1.1 ohm cm(2)) for the NCCO(Sa).
Titulo: Cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance suggests adsorption of oxygen by cathode as rate-limiting step.
Titulo: Cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The proposed mechanochemical reaction is useful as a technique for the synthesis of materials with submicron-sized crystallites.
Titulo: Cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
